article.description: Saint Francis shuts down Robert Morris 23-3
article.headline: Saint Francis shuts down Robert Morris 23-3
article.linkText: Saint Francis shuts down Robert Morris 23-3
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Kyle Harbridge rushed for 110 yards and scored two touchdowns to help Saint Francis put away Robert Morris 23-3 Saturday. The Red Flash (5-6, 3-3 Northeast) jumped ahead early as Max Ward hit Harbridge for a 44-yard touchdown on the third play of the opening drive. Harbridge scored again 3 1/2 minutes later on a 10-yard run set up from an interception by Lorenzo Jerome. Lance Geesey added three field goals for Saint Francis, with his third making the score 23-3 in the third quarter. Connor Shennan kicked a field goal at the end of the first half to give Robert Morris (5-6, 3-3) their only points. They finished with four turnovers and were held to just 11 yards rushing. Marcus Prather and Paul Jones combined to go 16-for-45 with 219 yards and three interceptions for the Colonials. Ward was 10 of 18 for 164 yards with two interceptions.
